response.message:
Well, as someone always looking for new ways of sticking it to the man, I recommend:

1. Something like Stylish for Chrome (they all seem a bit buggy, but hey, rebellion isn't perfect)

2. 
    div.topbar {
        width: 100%; background-color: rgba(33, 33, 33, 0.87); 
        //Or mauvelous, anyone?
        height: 34px; top: 0px; position:fixed;
    }
    body.new-topbar {
        padding-top: 34px;
    }
    #notify-container, #overlay-header, #custom-header {
        // I dunno, but thought better safe...
        top: 0px; position: fixed;
    }

3. Howz your corporate branding now, SO? ;)

Now we can all be happy and stop complaining. You're welcome ^_^

Power to the people...

@Swati (and others): The UserStyle for a light bar is already there. I combined several suggestions from http://meta.stackoverflow.com/questions/210041/gallery-of-custom-styles-and-or-scripts-for-the-top-bar/210050 and from this blog (light, floating, etc.), and put the "Mash-Up" on UserStyles:

http://userstyles.org/styles/95794/stackexchange-multicollider-superdropdown-fixes

Tested with SO, Android, DBA, AskUbuntu, SuperUser, ServerFault. Should work on other *.stackexchange.com sites as well, but I didn't test them all ;)
